The company had posted a standalone net profit of Rs 132.67 crore in the year-ago quarter  TVS Motor said in a BSE filing. @TVSMotor #TVS
#TVS Motor - Total exports of two and three-wheelers in the third quarter stood at 1.40 lakh units as against 99 000 units in the year-ago period  registering a growth of 41.4 per cent
#TVS Motor - Three-wheeler sales posted a growth of 67.7 per cent in Q3 to 26 968 units in the quarter under review
#TVS Motor - Scooter sales also increased to 2.69 lakh units in Q3 from 2.21lakh units same period last fiscal  a growth of 21.6 per cent
#TVS Motor - Motorcycle sales were up 26.7 per cent to 3.14 lakh units in third quarter as compared to 2.48 lakh units in the same period last fiscal
#TVS Motor - During the quarter ended December 2017  the overall two-wheeler sales  including exports  grew 13.8 per cent to 7.99 lakh units as against 7.03 lakh units in the year-ago period
#TVS Motor - Revenue from operations was at Rs 3 684.95 crore during the Q3  In the same quarter previous fiscal  the figure stood at Rs 3 239.55 crore
#TVS Motor - Chennai-based TVS Motor Co reported 16.34 per cent increase in standalone net profit at Rs 154.25 crore for the third quarter ended December 31  riding on robust sales growth.
